==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[senatus]]'', '''senate''', from ''[[senex]]'', '''old'''

===Noun===
'''senate'''
# In a [[bicameral]] [[legislative]] system, the [[upper house]] or chamber.
# A group of old, wise men
#: ''A mighty Senate; -- some, whose white hair shone / Like mountain snow, mild, beautiful, and blind;'' -- Percy Shelley.

